description:
Introduced by your host, The Bloke, a Victorian undertaker, who I dress as at conventions to promote the magazine. Bloke's Terrible Tomb of Terror is a homage to the classic horror anthology magazines that we grew up loving.

This is an ongoing, self-published series, with thirteen issues currently available and two collected editions. Voted Best Anthology Of 2013 in the Ghastly Awards.

description: Albert the Alien's friend Miranda introduces him to a cat for the first time, and the encounter is anything but normal. Illustrated by guest artist Jennifer Blake (My Little Pony).
name: Cat Encounters

description: Albert the Alien tries to understand the strange holiday of Halloween, our obsession with candy, and how to get rid of a possessed TV. Illustrated by guest artist Zach Miller (Joe and Monkey).
name: Halloween (Mis)Adventures

description: To Albert the Alien, even things like selfies, going out to a restaurant, and trying candy for the first time can be an adventure! Illustrated by guest artist Val Hochberg (Kick-Girl).
name: Earth (Mis)Adventures

description: There's an unidentified flying object headed straight for the school, and the government thinks that Albert the Alien has something to do with it? Is the object sent to conquor our planet? Or is there another nefarious force behind this dastardly device?
name: Chapter 5

description: The countdown to the end of life as we know it has begun, and at the center of it all is 7th grade student Albert the Alien. As the UFO arrives on Earth, Albert must come to grips with the fact that he's different from everyone else. But does that make him a burden, or the best hope to save the school?
name: Chapter 6

description: Life has been pretty strange since Albert the Alien first came to Earth - but things are about to get even more strange! Robot hall monitors have started to take over the school, and only Albert and friends can save the day? What do they have to do with the mysterious Locker #13, and can Albert solve the mystery of the locker thief?
name: Chapter 7

description: Life has been pretty strange since Albert the Alien first came to Earth - but things are about to get even more strange! Robot hall monitors have started to take over the school, and only Albert and friends can save the day? What do they have to do with the mysterious Locker #13, and can Albert solve the mystery of the locker thief?
name: Chapter 8

description: Albert the Alien is back, and his English class is putting on a 7th grade play of Romeo and Juliet...in space! However, the popular kids aren't too happy about the casting of the play. And who is the new artsy kid in class?
name: Chapter 9

description: Albert the Alien has been selected to play a crucial role in the upcoming 7th grade school play of Romeo and Juliet...in space! But someone is trying to sabbotage the play for their own gain. Can Albert and friends save the play before the curtains close?
name: Chapter 10

description: Someone has stolen the Heston Heights Middle School mascot! Albert and his friends must figure out who took the symbol of their school spirit before it's too late.
name: Chapter 11

description: Albert the Alien and friends sneak into their rival school to find out who stole their mascot, and challenge the bullies to a game of alien sports! Can Albert save the mascot before the Homecoming Game, or will the bullies beat him at his own game?
name: Chapter 12

description: Albert the Alien takes his first fieldtrip to the Nimoy History Museum. But when school bully Wally steals Albert's alien Controller, he brings an evil Mummy King back to life! Will Albert be able to save the day, or will this first fieldtrip be Albert's last?
name: Chapter 13

description: With his friends turned into a mummy army, it's up to Albert the Alien to get back his alien Controller and stop the evil Mummy King once and for all!
name: Chapter 14

description: During his speech for the Homecoming King and Queen elections, Gerty and Draven uncover the mystery behind the robot substitute teachers. Will they be able to stop the diabolical machines from taking over the school forever?
name: Chapter 15

description: Albert the Alien is looking forward to his first Homecoming Dance on Earth, but there's a problem - all of the chaperones have been replaced by robots! His best friend, Gerty Greyson, has gone missing! Can Albert get to the bottom of this mystery before he's expelled from school forever?
name: Chapter 16

description: This is the final battle between Albert the Alien and the robot substitute teachers. Will Albert be able to help his human friends regain control of their school?
name: Chapter 17
